    <title>Introduction to HTML5</title>
    <content>HTML5 is the latest version of the HTML standard used to structure content on the web.</content>

    <content>It introduces new semantic elements, attributes, and behaviors that simplify web development and improve accessibility.</content>

    <content>Here are some examples of new semantic elements introduced in HTML5:</content>
    <ul>
        <li><important>&lt;header&gt;</important>: Defines introductory content or a navigational link section.</li>
        <li><important>&lt;nav&gt;</important>: Defines a set of navigation links.</li>
        <li><important>&lt;section&gt;</important>: Represents a standalone section of content.</li>
        <li><important>&lt;article&gt;</important>: Represents self-contained content like blog posts or news articles.</li>
        <li><important>&lt;footer&gt;</important>: Defines footer for a document or section.</li>
    </ul>

    <content>HTML5 also introduces new input types to improve forms:</content>
    <ul>
        <li><important>email</important>: Validates email addresses automatically.</li>
        <li><important>date</important>: Provides a date picker.</li>
        <li><important>range</important>: Adds a slider UI.</li>
        <li><important>color</important>: Adds a color picker.</li>
    </ul>

    <content>Example of a new input type:</content>
    <code>&lt;input type="email" name="user_email"&gt;</code>

